Specific_Instance_Per_Administrative_Are.Num: Over 300 buildings, including homes, businesses, and public facilities were either damaged or completely destroyed.
Up to 100 structures sustained some degree of damage, ranging from roof damage to complete destruction.
Portions of the French Quarter were flooded
A EF1 tornado was reported near New Orleans on July 10, snapping several trees and ripping the roof off a house
A possible tornado damaged two homes
Power lines knocked down by fallen trees in the Metairie area cut power to 5,140 electricity customers
All electricity customers in Grand Isle lost power
The Clark County Humane Society in Arkadelphia was drenched by floodwaters, killing a puppy
The police department building and the county jail were damaged by flash flooding
